# Algolia Search Integration

Modern search integration for {{ project_name }} using Algolia's powerful search infrastructure.

## Features

- **InstantSearch**: Real-time search results as you type
- **Autocomplete**: Search-as-you-type with suggestions
- **Multi-Index Search**: Search across multiple data sources simultaneously
- **Faceted Search**: Filter results by categories, tags, and attributes
- **Geo Search**: Location-based search results
- **AI-Powered Ranking**: Intelligent result ordering
- **Analytics**: Track searches, clicks, and conversions
- **Typo Tolerance**: Handles misspellings automatically
- **Synonyms**: Custom synonym management
- **React Hooks**: Modern hooks-based API

## Setup

### 1. Environment Variables

Add these to your `.env.local`:

```bash
# Algolia Configuration
NEXT_PUBLIC_ALGOLIA_APP_ID=your_app_id
NEXT_PUBLIC_ALGOLIA_SEARCH_KEY=your_search_key
ALGOLIA_ADMIN_KEY=your_admin_key  # Server-side only, never expose to frontend
```

Get your API keys from: https://www.algolia.com/account/api-keys/all

### 2. Install Dependencies

The required dependencies are already included in `package.json`:

```json
{
  "dependencies": {
    "algoliasearch": "^5.0.0"
  }
}
```

### 3. Configure Indices

Update `client.ts` to add your custom indices:

```typescript
export const SEARCH_INDICES = {
  PRODUCTS: 'products',
  BLOG_POSTS: 'blog_posts',
  DOCUMENTATION: 'documentation',
  // Add your custom indices here
} as const;
```

## Usage

### Client-Side Search

#### Basic Search

```tsx
import { useInstantSearch } from '@/integrations/search/algolia';

function ProductSearch() {
  const { query, setQuery, hits, isSearching, pagination } = useInstantSearch({
    indexName: 'products',
    searchParams: {
      hitsPerPage: 20,
      facets: ['category', 'brand'],
    },
  });

  return (
    <div>
      <input
        value={query}
        onChange={(e) => setQuery(e.target.value)}
        placeholder="Search products..."
        className="w-full px-4 py-2 border rounded"
      />

      {isSearching && <div>Searching...</div>}

      <div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 mt-4">
        {hits.map((hit) => (
          <div key={hit.objectID} className="border p-4 rounded">
            <h3>{hit.name}</h3>
            <p>${hit.price}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div className="flex gap-2 mt-4">
        <button
          onClick={pagination.previousPage}
          disabled={pagination.page === 0}
        >
          Previous
        </button>
        <span>
          Page {pagination.page + 1} of {pagination.nbPages}
        </span>
        <button
          onClick={pagination.nextPage}
          disabled={pagination.page >= pagination.nbPages - 1}
        >
          Next
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

#### Autocomplete

```tsx
import { useAutocomplete } from '@/integrations/search/algolia';

function SearchAutocomplete() {
  const { query, setQuery, suggestions, isLoading, selectItem } = useAutocomplete({
    indexName: 'products',
    hitsPerPage: 5,
    onSelect: (product) => {
      router.push(`/products/${product.objectID}`);
    },
  });

  return (
    <div className="relative">
      <input
        value={query}
        onChange={(e) => setQuery(e.target.value)}
        placeholder="Search..."
        className="w-full px-4 py-2 border rounded"
      />

      {isLoading && <div className="absolute mt-1">Loading...</div>}

      {suggestions.length > 0 && (
        <ul className="absolute w-full bg-white border rounded mt-1 shadow-lg">
          {suggestions.map((item) => (
            <li
              key={item.objectID}
              onClick={() => selectItem(item)}
              className="px-4 py-2 hover:bg-gray-100 cursor-pointer"
            >
              {item.name}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}
```

#### Multi-Index Search (Federated Search)

```tsx
import { useMultiSearch } from '@/integrations/search/algolia';

function FederatedSearch() {
  const { query, setQuery, results, isSearching } = useMultiSearch({
    queries: [
      { indexName: 'products', hitsPerPage: 3 },
      { indexName: 'blog_posts', hitsPerPage: 3 },
      { indexName: 'documentation', hitsPerPage: 3 },
    ],
    searchQuery: '',
  });

  return (
    <div>
      <input
        value={query}
        onChange={(e) => setQuery(e.target.value)}
        placeholder="Search everything..."
      />

      {results?.map((result, index) => (
        <section key={index} className="mb-8">
          <h2 className="text-xl font-bold mb-4">
            {result.hits[0]?.__indexName}
          </h2>
          <div className="space-y-2">
            {result.hits.map((hit) => (
              <div key={hit.objectID}>{hit.title || hit.name}</div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </section>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Server-Side Indexing

#### Index Single Object

```typescript
import { saveObject } from '@/integrations/search/algolia';

// Index a product
await saveObject({
  indexName: 'products',
  object: {
    objectID: 'prod_123',
    name: 'MacBook Pro 16"',
    description: 'Powerful laptop for professionals',
    price: 2499,
    category: 'electronics',
    brand: 'Apple',
    inStock: true,
    rating: 4.8,
    reviewCount: 1234,
  },
});
```

#### Batch Index Multiple Objects

```typescript
import { saveObjects } from '@/integrations/search/algolia';

// Index multiple products
const products = await db.products.findMany();

await saveObjects({
  indexName: 'products',
  objects: products.map((product) => ({
    objectID: product.id,
    name: product.name,
    description: product.description,
    price: product.price,
    category: product.category,
    brand: product.brand,
    inStock: product.inStock,
    rating: product.rating,
    reviewCount: product.reviewCount,
  })),
});
```

#### Update Object

```typescript
import { partialUpdateObject } from '@/integrations/search/algolia';

// Update only specific fields
await partialUpdateObject({
  indexName: 'products',
  objectID: 'prod_123',
  attributes: {
    price: 2299, // Updated price
    inStock: false,
  },
});
```

#### Delete Object

```typescript
import { deleteObject } from '@/integrations/search/algolia';

await deleteObject({
  indexName: 'products',
  objectID: 'prod_123',
});
```

### Configure Index Settings

```typescript
import { configureIndex } from '@/integrations/search/algolia';

await configureIndex({
  indexName: 'products',
  settings: {
    // Searchable attributes (in order of importance)
    searchableAttributes: [
      'name',
      'brand',
      'category',
      'description',
    ],

    // Attributes for faceting (filtering)
    attributesForFaceting: [
      'category',
      'brand',
      'filterOnly(inStock)',
      'searchable(tags)',
    ],

    // Custom ranking (tie-breaker)
    customRanking: [
      'desc(popularity)',
      'desc(rating)',
      'asc(price)',
    ],

    // Highlighting
    attributesToHighlight: ['name', 'description'],

    // Snippeting
    attributesToSnippet: ['description:20'],

    // Typo tolerance
    typoTolerance: true,
    minWordSizefor1Typo: 4,
    minWordSizefor2Typos: 8,

    // Results per page
    hitsPerPage: 20,

    // Remove stop words
    removeStopWords: ['en'],

    // Query languages
    queryLanguages: ['en'],
  },
});
```

### Manage Synonyms

```typescript
import { saveSynonym } from '@/integrations/search/algolia';

// Add synonyms
await saveSynonym({
  indexName: 'products',
  objectID: 'laptop-synonym',
  synonyms: ['laptop', 'notebook', 'macbook', 'computer'],
  type: 'synonym',
});

// One-way synonym (iPhone -> mobile phone, but not vice versa)
await saveSynonym({
  indexName: 'products',
  objectID: 'iphone-synonym',
  synonyms: ['iPhone', 'mobile phone'],
  type: 'oneWaySynonym',
});
```

## Advanced Features

### Geo Search

```typescript
import { search } from '@/integrations/search/algolia';

// Search near a location
const results = await search({
  indexName: 'stores',
  query: 'coffee',
  aroundLatLng: '37.7749,-122.4194', // San Francisco coordinates
  aroundRadius: 5000, // 5km radius
});
```

### Filtering

```typescript
// Numeric filters
const results = await search({
  indexName: 'products',
  query: 'laptop',
  filters: 'price >= 1000 AND price <= 2000',
});

// Facet filters
const results = await search({
  indexName: 'products',
  query: 'laptop',
  filters: 'category:electronics AND brand:Apple',
});

// Multiple filters with OR
const results = await search({
  indexName: 'products',
  query: 'laptop',
  filters: '(brand:Apple OR brand:Dell) AND category:electronics',
});
```

